- Double-check JSX syntax for common mistakes:
  - Proper comma separation in import lists: `import { A, B, C } from ...`
  - Component names have no spaces: `AlertDialogFooter` not `AlertDialog Footer`
  - Self-closing tags where appropriate: `<Input />` not `<Input></Input>`
- Use meaningful variable names and avoid abbreviations
- Ensure proper nesting of HTML elements
- Handle conditional rendering safely with proper boolean checks
- Use proper JSX attribute syntax:
  - Boolean attributes: `disabled` not `disabled={true}`
  - Event handlers: `onClick={() => handleClick()}` with proper typing
  - className instead of class: `className="text-lg"` not `class="text-lg"`
- Escape special characters properly in JSX text content
- Use fragments `<>` or `<React.Fragment>` instead of unnecessary wrapper divs
- Ensure all JSX elements are properly closed and nested
- Use proper key props for all list items: `key={item.id}` with unique, stable values
- Handle undefined/null values safely in JSX expressions with fallbacks
- Use logical AND (`&&`) carefully - prefer ternary for complex conditions
- Apply consistent indentation and formatting for readability
- Group related JSX elements logically with proper spacing
- Use descriptive variable names for complex JSX expressions
- Extract complex conditional logic into variables before JSX return